              "label": {
                "en": [
                  "Sidney J. Parnes and Harold F. Harding eds., The Sourcebook for Creative Thinking, 1962"
                ]
              },
              "summary": {
                "en": [
                  "Traditionally, psychologists used ink blot tests to peer into peoples’ subconscious. Creativity researchers were interested not in the underlying meaning of what their subjects saw in the random shapes but rather their originality, which researchers quantified to calculate a measure of creative ability."
                ]
              },
