              "label": {
                "en": [
                  "Sidney J. Parnes and Harold F. Harding eds., The Sourcebook for Creative Thinking, 1962"
                ]
              },
              "summary": {
                "en": [
                  "Researchers at Berkeley’s IPAR asked subjects to create mosaics with colored tiles. The examples on the left were produced by the “non-creative” control group of randomly selected students, while those on the right were produced by prominent figures rated highly creative by their peers. The researchers concluded that creative people naturally prefer asymmetrical figures."
                ]
              },
